claimVested(uint256,uint256).details: This is a public function that should be called periodically by a keeper or incentivized actor. The collected tokens are held by this contract for redemption.

params.count: The number of NFTs to process in this batch.
params.startIndex: The starting index in the heldNFTs array to process.

params._underlyingToken: The address of the underlying asset being vested (e.g., SONIC).
params._vsToken: The address of the vS token contract.

deposit(uint256).details: This is a one-way bridge. The NFT is permanently locked.

params.nftId: The ID of the Sonic NFT to deposit.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.amount: The amount of vS tokens to burn.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setNFTContract(address).details: Can only be called once by the owner. This is a critical security step to ensure the vault only ever interacts with a verified, audited fNFT contract.

params._sonicNFT: The address of the Sonic vesting NFT contract.

totalAssets().details: The total amount of redeemable assets held by the vault.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

claimVested(uint256,uint256).notice: Claims currently vested tokens from a batch of NFTs held by the vault.

deposit(uint256).notice: Deposits an fNFT and mints vS tokens for its full future value.

redeem(uint256).notice: Burns vS tokens to redeem a proportional share of the underlying tokens held by the vault.

setNFTContract(address).notice: Sets the official fNFT contract address.
